Issues.Body:
### Description

I create an application that working on the tasktray. The user can hide the window and show it again from the tasktray.
However, when redisplayed via Remote Desktop, the window turns black.

### Reproduction Steps

1. Create the new WPF application from template.
2. Change source code in **App.xaml.cs**.

```
    public partial class App : Application
    {
        private System.Windows.Forms.NotifyIcon _notifyIcon;

        private MainWindow _win = null;
        protected override void OnStartup(StartupEventArgs e)
        {
            base.OnStartup(e);

            var icon = GetResourceStream(new Uri("test.ico", UriKind.Relative)).Stream;

            _notifyIcon = new System.Windows.Forms.NotifyIcon
            {
                Visible = true,
                Icon = new System.Drawing.Icon(icon),
                Text = "SampleApp",
            };

            _notifyIcon.MouseClick += (s, er) =>
            {
                if (er.Button == System.Windows.Forms.MouseButtons.Left)
                {
                    ShowMainWindow();
                }
            };
            
            if (_win == null)
            {
                _win = new MainWindow();
                _win.WindowStartupLocation = WindowStartupLocation.CenterScreen;

                _win.Closing += (s, ea) =>
                {
                    _win.Visibility = Visibility.Collapsed;   //the window turns black
                    //_win.Visibility = Visibility.Hidden;   //if use Visibility.Hidden, the window not turns black.
                    ea.Cancel = true;
                };
            }
        }

        protected override void OnExit(ExitEventArgs e)
        {
            _notifyIcon.Dispose();
            base.OnExit(e);
        }

        private void ShowMainWindow()
        {
            if (_win != null)
            {
                _win.Show();
            }
        }
    }
```
3. Delete `StartupUri="MainWindow.xaml"` from **App.xaml**.
4. Build the solution.
5. Start the application. You must check that the application working on the tasktray.
6. Close the window. You must check that the application working on the tasktray, again.
7. Connect to machine of the step 6 using Remote Desktop(mstsc.exe)
8. Redisplay the application from the task tray.

### Expected behavior

If you use `_win.Visibility = Visibility.Collapsed;`, the window turns black in step 8.
If you use  `_win.Visibility = Visibility.Hidden;`, the window not turns black in step 8.

